THOUGHT: The crash still occurs, but now it's an assertion "isa<> used on a null pointer". This suggests that `OrigInc` or `WideInc` might be null. Looking at the stack trace, line 828 in `ScalarEvolutionExpander.cpp` is where `isa<BinaryOperator>` is called. My modification added `isa<BinaryOperator>(OrigInc)`, but if `OrigInc` is null, `isa` will assert. I need to also check for null pointers. Let me update the function to check for null first.

```bash
sed -i '828,832c\  if (!OrigInc || !WideInc)
    return false;
  if (!isa<BinaryOperator>(OrigInc) || !isa<BinaryOperator>(WideInc))
    return false;
  return match(OrigInc, m_c_BinOp(m_Specific(OrigPhi), m_Value())) &&
         match(WideInc, m_c_BinOp(m_Specific(WidePhi), m_Value())) &&
         OrigInc->getOpcode() == WideInc->getOpcode();' ./llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/ScalarEvolutionExpander.cpp
```

